        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 4.  HOSPITALIZED MINORS' RIGHT TO HEARING
Art. 1411.  Right to hearing
A minor or his attorney shall have the right to demand a hearing to determine whether the minor should receive treatment on an inpatient basis, be discharged from the treatment facility, or placed in a less restrictive setting.</p>
        </content>
